The paper discusses a tool for analyzing and disambiguating cited references in a publication set, which is relevant to the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The focus on standardization of cited references is also relevant to the field of cybernetics (cs.CY). The use of the tool to study the historical roots of a research field suggests a potential connection to social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the use of bibliometric analysis and graph theory suggests a potential connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
